<P>
   GEEWAX-Y2K-COLUMN _ On many things Christians agree, but not on
how to view the impending arrival of a third millennium. (Geewax,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   EZZARD-COLUMN _ ATLANTA _ Gov. Roy Barnes still winces over the
slogan his opponent, Guy Milner, used in the last election: ``Roy
Barnes _ too liberal for Georgia.'' But it is precisely because
there's nothing liberal about Barnes' record or style that he's
been able to sell a progressive transportation initiative to a
Legislature that moves like molasses. (Ezzard, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BORDERS-COLUMN - JASPER, Texas _ There's no circus here in
what's being dubbed as the East Texas Trial of the Century. Hardly
anybody is milling around the square. Cops outnumber hangers-on
outside. Inside, the media seem to outnumber other spectators as
they cover the so-called dragging-death trial. (Borders,
Nacogdoches Daily Sentinel) MOVED.
