   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio. _ Former CNN chief, and
one-time outdoor advertiser, Ted Turner seems to spend an awful lot
of time trying to pry his foot out of his mouth. On Tuesday, in an
address to the National Family Planning and Reproductive
Association in Washington, he tells a Polish joke in reference to
the pope.
</P>
<P>
   On Wednesday he issues an apology to the Catholic League, an
anti-defamation group that didn't think he was very funny. And that
was last week. Wonder what he's up to this week. (Elizabeth
Schuett, a teacher and writer in Gibsonburg, Ohio, writes twice a
week for Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
