A4300 &Cx1f; tad-z
u f &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-MAC-REPORT23-COX     02-22 0414
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MAC-REPORT23-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    New three-screen format makes MacInTax program easier to figure
 &HT;    By Charles Haddad
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   You know it must be tax time when Intuit releases its latest
version of MacInTax.
</P>
<P>
   This year's update is a keeper. Intuit has made great strides in
improving MacInTax's ease of use. The program is both easier to
navigate and configure.
</P>
<P>
   The program is also more intuitive, anticipating questions
you'll be asked by the Internal Revenue Service.
</P>
<P>
   Longtime users of MacInTax will notice a new look. The main
screen is divided into three panels. This look is a little
overwhelming at first, but once learned, functions well.
</P>
<P>
   The top panel is MacInTax's traditional one. It is here the
program questions you about your finances and tax status. The
answers are plugged into the appropriate tax forms, which are
viewable in a second panel below the first one.
</P>
<P>
   The forms are filled out in real time as you answer MacInTax's
questions. For example, type in the information from your W-2 form
in the top question panel, and the answers are automatically filled
into the right boxes in the IRS forms.
</P>
<P>
   The third panel runs along the left side of the screen and is
the way you navigate through the program. It works much the same
way as a similar panel in Microsoft's Internet Explorer Web
browser.
</P>
<P>
   The third panel lists a series of bookmarks. Highlight and click
on one of them, and you'll jump to the corresponding place in both
the official forms and the interview panel.
</P>
<P>
   In the past, it has been difficult to go backtrack in the
interview process. No longer. Intuit has finally made it easy to
change your answers, delete forms or add new ones.
</P>
<P>
   Another nice feature is the amount of your refund, or lack
thereof, posted in the upper right corner of the interview panel.
The figure changes as you enter tax data, so you can see in real
time how you're faring.
</P>
<P>
   As in the past, MacInTax will automatically review your return.
With this version, though, Intuit has improved the program's
ability to detect deductions you have missed.
</P>
<P>
   MacInTax, available in most computer stores, can also be found
online and in various Mac mail-order catalogs. It retails for about
$50 for the deluxe version, which includes a library of video clip
interviews with tax experts.
</P>
<P>
   Haddad writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
