<HEADLINE>
`RONIN' CRUISES; SUPER FOOTBALL GAME IN DVD 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``Ronin'' _ If it's action you want, it's action
you get in this carefully crafted suspenser with the dependable
Robert De Niro leading the way. The chase scenes are the best since
``Bullitt,'' and they're even better in the DVD format where the
image density and sound quality add to the adrenaline rush.
</P>
<P>
   ``Pecker'' _ The devilish John Waters is up to his old tricks in
this story about a kid who becomes a famous celebrity photographer.
Frankly, Waters has cleaned up his act, losing some of the filth
that made him so interesting to some. But this is a pretty funny
movie about the celebrity culture that Waters wallows in.
</P>
<P>
   ``Super Bowl XXXII'' _ Not XXXIII, but DVD. The Broncos-Packers
1998 Super Bowl in the DVD format is remarkable for pigheads who
can't get enough pigskin. It allows the viewer to see plays from
dozens of angles. You can become your own TV sports director for
$29.95 from Polygram.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   GAY TELETUBBIES?: For those who want to check out Jerry
Falwell's bizarre theories on homosexuality as it relates to the
Teletubbies, check out ``Teletubbies: Nursery Rhymes'' for $14.95
from Warner Home Video. Frankly, there aren't many who share
Falwell's view about the innocent little British imports. The most
dangerous moment comes when Po rescues Miss Muffet from the spider.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: March 2: ``Dark City,'' ``Tom and Jerry: The
Movie,'' ``A Winter Tan,'' ``The Island of Dr. Moreau.'' March 9:
``What Dreams May Come,'' ``Dead Man on Campus,'' ``Black Dog,''
``Slam,'' ``Somebody Is Waiting.'' March 16: ``The Waterboy,''
``Bulworth,'' ``No Laughing Matter,'' ``Living Out Loud,'' ``One
True Thing,'' ``Polish Wedding,'' ``Paul Monette: The Brink of
Summer's End,'' ``The Wonderful Ice Cream Suit,'' ``Who the Hell Is
Juliette?'' March 23: ``Pleasantville,'' ``Firelight,'' ``Bride of
Chucky,'' ``Jerry Springer's Ringmaster,'' ``From Dusk Till Dawn
2,'' ``Strike!'' March 30: ``The Rugrats Movie,'' ``Mutual Needs.''
April 6: ``A Soldier's Daughter Never Cries,'' ``I Still Know What
You Did Last Summer,'' ``An Unexpected Life,'' ``Meet Joe Black,''
``The Dentist 2.'' April 13: ``The Tempest,'' ``Bug Buster,''
``Conspirators of Pleasure.'' April 20: ``A Bug's Life.'' April 27:
``Happiness.'' May 4: ``Babe: Pig in the City.'' May 11: ``Another
Day in Paradise.''
</P>
</TEXT>
