<P>
   WASHINGTON/POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-WASHINGTON _ Gov. George W. Bush is doing more politicking
than policy-making during his trip to the nation's capital. He's
been meeting with political friends, Republican governors and has
skipped out on much of the National Governor's Association events.
Also Monday, Bush and the other governors met with President
Clinton. (Greenberger, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   NATION
</P>
<P>
   JASPERDEATH-TRIAL _ JASPER, Texas _ After his arrest in the
dragging death of a black man last summer, Bill King wrote letters
to a co- defendant saying they both probably would get off, and if
they didn't they would at least be remembered for the crime. The
testimony came Monday as prosecutors prepared to wrap up their case
against King. The defense could begin this afternoon. (Gamino,
Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
