<P>
   ``Yesterday, President Clinton told reporters that his
mother-in-law has moved into the White House. The President said he
allowed her to move in because she's all alone and she doesn't have
a bad body.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's been reported in a magazine that when Demi Moore is
filming a movie, she will only wash her hair with Evian water. Not
only that, she'll only wash her breasts with cleansers that don't
harm plastic.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Diane Sawyer is very upset because the other day she did an
interview with a zookeeper and during the interview a chimpanzee
sat on top of her head. Afterwards, Sam Donaldson called up to say,
'Don't feel bad. I wear a chimp on my head everyday.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``Earlier tonight, George Clooney's character on 'E.R.' left the
show because he was caught helping a patient with an assisted
suicide. Ironically, the patient was a woman who'd lost her will to
live because George Clooney is leaving 'E.R.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``In a recent interview, Lucy Lawless who plays Xena the Warrior
Princess, said she likes being a gay icon even though she's married
with children. In a different interview, Tinky Winky said the same
thing.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Political experts are saying that if Hillary Clinton does run
for Senate, she may end up expressing views that conflict with her
husband's. Reportedly, they have very different opinions on foreign
policy, capital punishment and threesomes.''
</P>
<P>
   ``In a recent interview, Celine Dion vehemently denied that
she's anorexic. However, Celine did admit that her music is one of
the leading causes of bulimia.''
</P>
<P>
   ``During the last couple of years, one million additional people
started riding New York's subways. In fact, people say the subways
are so crowded these days you can barely urinate without hitting
someone.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The other day, Michael Jackson broke his wrist and had to be
taken to the hospital. Apparently, when Jackson got to the
hospital, his only request was that his doctor be Doogie Howser.''
</P>
