moved into the White House. I want to tell you something, there is
nothing like a long visit from the mother-in-law to take care of an
already shaky marriage.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I think President Clinton's already getting fed up with his
mother-in-law. Earlier today, he asked Vernon Jordan to get her a
job at Revlon.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I wonder what Linda Tripp has given up for Lent because I know
last year, she gave up Monica Lewinsky.''
</P>
<P>
   ``President Clinton is back up there in New Hampshire...It's a
very nostalgic trip for President Clinton, returning to New
Hampshire. That's the state where he first lied about sex.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DAVID-LETTERMAN LATE SHOW TOP TEN &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Things You Don't Want to Hear from a Hot Dog Vendor'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   10. ``I trapped the meat myself.''
</P>
<P>
   9. ``Can we hurry this up, I have to meet my parole officer.''
</P>
<P>
   8. ``Botulism, schmotulism, am I right, Vicky?''
</P>
<P>
   7. ``Would you like to smear mustard on me?''
</P>
<P>
   6. ``I kissed every one for good luck.''
</P>
<P>
   5. ``There's a zoo in every bite.''
</P>
<P>
   4. ``Did you see me on 60 Minutes' last night?''
</P>
<P>
   3. ``Would you like a drink to wash down this uncooked mystery
tube?''
</P>
<P>
   2. ``I'll see you in the emergency room, genius!''
</P>
<P>
   1. ``You're my first customer in eight weeks.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BILL'S WORLD &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Scientists report being able to slow the speed of light to 38
mph. Even that's faster than the speed of the recent impeachment
trial.
</P>
<P>
   _(Bill Tammeus, The Kansas City Star)
</P>
