<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM 'WEEKEND UPDATE' ON NBC's 'SATURDAY NIGHT LIVE' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Earlier this week President Clinton flew to Mexico for
meetings with President Ernesto Zedillo. What a perfect way for
President Clinton to show the country he's a changed man. He goes
on spring break.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The race for Senate in New York is already heating up. Mayor
Rudy Giuliani took a shot at Hillary Clinton yesterday, saying she
made a 'big mistake' by endorsing the Palestinian state. She
responded saying that big mistakes run in her family.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Juanita Hickey Broaddrick is the latest woman to come forward
to claim she was sexually assaulted by the President. In an
interview in today's Washington Post, she claims that in 1978 in a
Little Rock hotel room, Clinton bit her lips, tore her panty hose
and forced her to have sex with him. When asked for comment,
President Clinton said he couldn't have committed these acts
because on the date in question: 'I was sexually harassing Paula
Jones in another Little Rock hotel.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``This week, Boris Yeltsin warned President Clinton not to
launch air strikes against Yugoslavia, even if they fail to reach
peace with Kosovo rebels. Yeltsin received no response to his
threat because he was talking to a coat stand with a hat on it.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Yeltsin also met with officials from the European Union this
week to discuss plans for reviving Russia's failing economy. So far
the only plan they came up with was a Yakov Smirnoff Pay-Per-View
Special.''
</P>
<P>
   ``In her interview with Larry King, Linda Tripp said that if she
could meet Monica Lewinsky again, she would want to give her a hug.
This would be a classic case of adding injury to insult. Actually,
Tripp said she would hug Monica very tight, then Tripp would
unhinge her jaw and swallow her whole.''
</P>
<P>
   ``According to a poll in the New York Post, if Hillary Clinton
were to run for President against Elizabeth Dole, Dole would win in
a landslide. But if Hillary Clinton and Liddy Dole were to wrestle,
Hillary would have the advantage because of her mean spirit and
powerful legs.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The Army may start reaching out to high school dropouts in an
attempt to bolster recruitment. We're looking for a few good . .
okay forget it. Come on, dumb-ass, get in the truck. Just what we
need: an equivalency army.''
</P>
<P>
   ``More than two million people jammed New Orleans for Mardi
Gras, the festival of excessive eating drinking and sex, which ends
with the beginning of Lent, the Catholic 12-step program.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Eric Clapton is selling off most of his guitar collection to
raise money for a drug abuse center in Antigua. Meanwhile,
somewhere in Jersey, there's a kid selling pot to raise money for a
guitar. It's a crazy world, isn't it folks?''
</P>
<P>
   ``Scott Weiland of Stone Temple Pilots has pleaded guilty to
possession of heroin. He was given a harsh sentence of five to ten
VH-1 'Where Are They Nows.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``Bill Clinton is among the 118 people nominated for the Nobel
Peace Prize. The nominators say Clinton has helped contribute to
world peace. Upon hearing this, Saddam Hussein responded from under
pile of rubble: 'Hello! Don't you people have CNN?'''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; OPENING REMARKS FROM THE ``LATE SHOW with DAVID LETTERMAN'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Ladies and gentlemen, I'm sorry I may have to leave a little
early tonight. I found out I was just traded to Toronto.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Big news from the world of sports -- the Yankees have traded
David Wells...They traded him for Roger Clemens, a fine pitcher
there too. David Wells, don't kid yourself, he's so upset, I hear
he's stopped drinking.''
</P>
<P>
   ``You've probably heard stories about how Major League Baseball
players will be screwing around and stuff and I've heard that they
actually have pizza pies delivered during the game to the bullpen.
David Wells is the only pitcher I know who actually had pizzas
delivered to the mound.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Yeah, the trade -- David Wells, trading him away from the
Yankees -- is not very popular and, as a matter of fact, they're
already starting to talk about impeaching George Steinbrenner.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The New York Yankees have traded away our good friend David
Wells. He's going to Toronto... But it's not that bad a deal. In
return for David Wells, it's kind of complicated, here's what we
get: we get Roger Clemens, that's not a bad thing, Roger Clemens.
We also get George Clooney.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's fashion week here in New York City...and whenever we have
something like this, everybody gets into the spirit of fashion
week. For example, all week long, the New York City cops are
outlining bodies with colorful pastel chalk.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Yesterday was Chinese New Year.'' Let's see if I have this
straight: it's the Year of the Rabbit, and here's how dumb I am.
I'm still writing Year of the Pig' on my checks.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Also, down there in New Orleans, people were celebrating Mardi
Gras...Down there in New Orleans, Mardi Gras is a huge deal. Here
in New York City, Mardi Gras is not a big deal. In New York City,
people do not need an excuse, they do not need a special holiday to
get drunk and urinate in the streets.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Out there in California yesterday, they had a big auction and
they were selling off , they're trying to raise money now selling
off all of the remaining O.J. Simpson possessions. Big auction,
unbelievably successful, wildly successful -- they raised an
incredible amount of money, so much money in fact that at one
point, O.J. runs in and screams, Hey, wait a minute, is it too late
to add the knife?'''
</P>
<P>
   ``In honor of President's Day, today I took an intern up to my
office.''
</P>
<P>
   ``President Clinton for Valentine's Day...gave Hillary a lovely
heart-shaped pin...Here's what happened: President Clinton gave
Hillary the heart-shaped pin and then Bettie Currie asked her to
give it back.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The Clintons are in Mexico. President Clinton is in Mexico
City meeting with President Zedillo and Hillary is in Cancun
getting her groove back.''
</P>
<P>
   ``President Clinton is moving on, he's got things to do, so he
and his lovely wife Hillary are down in Mexico talking to President
Zedillo. President Clinton is trying to arrange a trade -- and I
think it's Hillary for Jennifer Lopez.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm very excited because President Clinton, recently impeached
President Clinton who was acquitted a couple of days ago, now is
nominated for a Nobel Peace Prize. He's being recognized for
maintaining that fragile peace between his wife and his
girlfriends.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Also, President Clinton is one of 118 people nominated for a
Nobel Peace Prize. However, historically, and I'll check this in
the encyclopedia when I get upstairs, I believe he's the only one
to ever be nominated for a Nobel Prize while having sex.''
</P>
<P>
   ``There was a recent poll about presidential
behavior...Fifty-six percent of Americans believe that President
Clinton has the lowest moral standards of any modern president. You
know what this means? This means this guy could win a third term.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Friday morning, Linda Tripp was on the Today' show, and
earlier tonight, Linda Tripp was on the Larry King Live' show, and
when you see Linda Tripp, it gives you a really good idea of what
J.Edgar Hoover looked like at cocktail parties.''
</P>
<P>
   ``More bad news for President Clinton -- did you hear about
this? He comes back from Mexico and his mother-in-law has moved
into the White House...Clinton's doing everything he can to get her
out of his hair, because, you know, it's trouble there having your
mother-in-law in the White House, so today he fixed her up with
Henry Hyde.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Did you hear about this? President Clinton's mother-in-law has
moved into the White House. I want to tell you something, there is
nothing like a long visit from the mother-in-law to take care of an
already shaky marriage.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I think President Clinton's already getting fed up with his
mother-in-law. Earlier today, he asked Vernon Jordan to get her a
job at Revlon.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I wonder what Linda Tripp has given up for Lent because I know
last year, she gave up Monica Lewinsky.''
</P>
<P>
   ``President Clinton is back up there in New Hampshire...It's a
very nostalgic trip for President Clinton, returning to New
Hampshire. That's the state where he first lied about sex.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DAVID-LETTERMAN LATE SHOW TOP TEN &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Things You Don't Want to Hear from a Hot Dog Vendor'' &LR;
</P>
