<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S 'THE TONIGHT SHOW WITH JAY LENO' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Some sad news: tonight was George Clooney's last episode of
'E.R.' Dr. Ross is gone. He said leaving 'E.R.' was a tough
decision, but he decided to do it after talking it over with his
advisors, David Caruso and Shelley Long.''  &QL; 
``Dole was on 'Good Morning America' this morning (Thursday). Now
that he's on Viagra, the producers use the Elvis shot: they only
shoot him from the waist up now.''
</P>
<P>
   ``The other night the L.A. Clippers lost in double overtime. I
think they're getting better. I mean, you still know they're going
to lose, now you just don't know when.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Linda Tripp was on 'Larry King' the other night. She says she
may still write a book. Wouldn't it be a lot easier to just release
the books on tape version? She already has that.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I guess Dennis Rodman hasn't signed yet with the Lakers; it's
not official. The reason is he said today, he first wants to talk
it over with his wife, Carmen Electra. That could take years! He
doesn't know where she lives!''
</P>
<P>
   ``You think Clinton has learned his lesson? I don't think so. As
soon as the trial ended, all White House interns were told to
report to spring training.''  &QL; 
``I'm watching the news today (Tuesday), I see people drunk and out
of their minds, I see men throwing beads, women bearing their
breasts. That Clinton victory party is unbelievable!''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; QUOTABLES FROM NBC'S 'LATE NIGHT WITH CONAN O'BRIEN &LR; '
</P>
<P>
   ``It was announced yesterday that President Clinton was
nominated for a Nobel Peace Prize. The President was singled out
for his effort to end violence in the Middle East and his attempts
to get Hillary to stop hitting him.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Yesterday President Clinton said that 'The tide of spring has
brought a new season for friendship.' In other words, it's getting
warmer out and he's horny again.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Mick Jagger took Jerry Hall skiing over Valentine's weekend to
try and patch up their relationship, but it didn't work. Apparently
everything was going fine until Jagger got somebody on the ski lift
pregnant.''
</P>
<P>
   ``This morning in the financial district, supermodel Rebecca
Romijn-Stamos helped promote the 'Sports Illustrated' swimsuit
issue by ringing the opening bell on Wall Street. Immediately
afterwards, the stock market rose about six inches.''
</P>
<P>
   ``According to a new poll by ABC News, only 17 percent of kids
say that they'd like to be President of the United States when they
grow up. Most kids today say they'd rather sleep with the President
and sign a huge book deal.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It was reported today that Air Force One recently started
serving a beer made from hemp. When asked about it, President
Clinton said, 'Hey, it's the only way to make Al Gore seem
interesting.'''
</P>
<P>
   ``Yesterday, President Clinton told reporters that his
mother-in-law has moved into the White House. The President said he
allowed her to move in because she's all alone and she doesn't have
a bad body.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's been reported in a magazine that when Demi Moore is
filming a movie, she will only wash her hair with Evian water. Not
