   &UR; NATIONAL-GENERAL  &LR;  (Will move in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   INDIAN-LAWSUIT (Dateline TK) _ For nearly a century, American
Indians have been asking the federal government for a simple
accounting of money and land held in trust for them since days of
treaty signing. Today, two Cabinet secretaries who oversee these
accounts were held in contempt of court by a federal judge who
accused the government of deceit and neglect in responding to the
largest lawsuit ever brought by Indians. By Timothy Egan.
</P>
<P>
   CHICAGO-MAYORAL (Chicago) _ Mayor Daley heads for resounding
re-election Tuesday with strong support from black voters. By Dirk
Johnson.
</P>
<P>
   NY-DRUNK-DRIVERS (New York) _ At least two cars are seized under
a new police crackdown on drunk drivers. By Ginger Thompson.
</P>
