<P>
   ``People must learn (to) be self-sufficient. Don't look to the
government when you make a mistake. Pull yourself up by your own
bootstraps, correct the mistake, and in the long run you'll be
better off for it, because you'll keep a core sense of values.''
</P>
<P>
   While he hasn't decided whether to seek re-election when his
four-year term is up, Ventura said he would not be a presidential
candidate in 2000.
</P>
<P>
   ``But 2004? Well, who knows? I could end up down the street here
in that big white house, or I could end up living in a hut on the
beaches at Kona _ I don't know right now what my future holds. I'm
just going to do the job that I am doing right now. And, as I've
done in all my life, we'll see what happens when a new day
arises.''
</P>
<P>
   (Story can end here. Optional add follows.)
</P>
<P>
   Ventura said he enjoyed meeting President Clinton and first lady
Hillary Rodham Clinton at a reception Sunday night at the White
House. At one point the Clintons and Venturas where the only ones
on the dance floor. Ventura said he was tempted to ask Mrs. Clinton
for a dance, but his wife told him, ``don't you dare.''
</P>
<P>
   Ventura said he felt snubbed last year when the World
Championship Wrestling Federation came to Minnesota and did not
recognize him or acknowledge his presence.
</P>
<P>
   ``I will tell you very honestly it hurt, personally it hurt.
Because I gave my heart and soul to the world of wrestling for a
number of years. And so, because of what happened there, I didn't
refer to wrestling at all in my inaugural address and I had no
wrestlers or anyone in wrestling who came to my inauguration.''
</P>
<P>
   Addressing reports that pro wrestler Hulk Hogan might run for
office in California, Ventura said Hogan should think about running
in Florida, where he lives, rather than in California. Ventura has
also said he thinks Mrs. Clinton should consider running for office
in Arkansas, rather than in New York, because she doesn't live
there.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
