   CYBERSCENE _ The World Wide Web is actually a useful place these
days. If you need demographic information from Des Moines, the
average rainfall for Medford, Ore., or a list of the books written
by Winston Churchill, you can find it with a few clicks of a mouse
button. (Husted, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
