<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Tuesday, Feb. 23 and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact William Toren at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   PANAVISION (Los Angeles) _ Advances in movie projection
technology make for an uncertain future at Panavision, the leading
maker of motion picture cameras. Although the digital projection
process as planned will still begin with 35mm film, Panavision is
hedging its bets by launching a digital camera department. By Dave
McNary.
</P>
<P>
   PINKERTON (Los Angeles) _ Pinkerton Inc., one of top names in
private security in the U.S. for more than a century, is being
acquired by Securitas AB of Sweden for $384 million in a deal
reported to result in the world's largest full-service security
firm. By Greg Wilcox.
</P>
