   RUSSIA-STEEL (Washington) _ The Clinton administration struck an
agreement with Russia on Monday to control Moscow's surging exports
of steel to the United States. The agreement represents an effort
to balance the bitter complaints of American steelmakers with
Washington's efforts to keep Russia's economic slide from
worsening. By David E. Sanger.
</P>
<P>
   (The story is scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET.)
