   (Top display)
</P>
<P>
   HSBC-ASIA (Hong Kong) _ Peering down from a conference room on
the 28th floor of the Hongkong and Shanghai Bank's spaceship-like
headquarters, it is hard to forget that one of the world's most
profitable banks was built on a geyser of wealth from this former
British colony. But when the bank announced its 1998 earnings here
on Monday, one could not help wondering what had happened to the
``Hong Kong'' in the bank's name. By Mark Landler.
</P>
