<HEADLINE>
A `TRUE' TAG TEAM: VENTURA, BUSH  

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Former pro-wrestler-turned-Minnesota governor Jesse
``the Body'' Ventura appears to have bonded with Texas Gov. George
W. Bush at the National Governors Association meeting.
</P>
<P>
   The hulking Ventura decided to look out for the much slighter
Bush on Monday outside the White House. As Bush was talking with
reporters, Ventura wandered over to urge the Republican governor to
get on the bus.
</P>
<P>
   ``Come on, George, we've got places to go,'' said Ventura, in
his booming voice.
</P>
<P>
   But Bush insisted on introducing Ventura to the Texas press,
which prompted the former wrestler to recall a line spoken by John
Wayne in the movie ``True Grit.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I haven't met a Texan yet who hasn't drunk dirty water from a
hoof print,'' Ventura quipped.
</P>
<P>
   Bush has called the 6-feet 4-inch Ventura a ``breath of fresh
air.''
</P>
<P>
   And while Ventura enjoyed joshing the Texas governor, he wasn't
ready to endorse Bush for president. Ventura, who won as a Reform
Party candidate, said he would like to see Colin Powell,retired
chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, run for president as an
independent candidate.
</P>
<P>
