   Off-lead story:
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-TALKS (Rambouillet, France) _ The Kosovo peace talks are
on the verge of breakdown, as five guerrillas from the Kosovo
Liberation Army refuse the exhortations of Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright to sign an agreement and are unpersuaded by a
last ditch visit from the Supreme Commander of NATO, Gen. Wesley
Clark. By Jane Perlez. (Scheduled to move by 8:15 p.m. ET in ``i''
news file.)
</P>
