<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-MICROSOFT-ANTITRUST-NYT (moved on Sunday, Feb. 21)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Feb. 21,
about an antitrust case against Intel misstated the actions of
Microsoft in a case now being tried in Federal court. Although
Microsoft succeeded in removing a judge in a previous antitrust
case against it, as well as a special master in the current case,
it has not sought the removal of Judge Thomas Penfield Jackson, who
is now hearing the case.
</P>
</TEXT>
